G. Chandler (first name and dates of birth and death unknown) was an English cricketer. Chandler played primarily as a wicketkeeper.
Chandler made a single first-class appearance for Hampshire in 1865, making his only appearance against Middlesex. Chandler made two stumpings and took a single catch behind the stumps.

response: *Gene G. Chandler (born 1947), Speaker of the New Hampshire House of Representatives (from 2017)
